------- Forwarded Message
While neither Bill nor I are part of the nic facility at SRI, we raise the
same points, there is or may be a plurality of domains for which a (or more)
authoritive namespace hosts exist, and the existing contract seems to be
satisfied...further, there is familiarity in the name "sri-nic.arpa", aka
"nic.sri.com", which is known to a rather large set of users.

From: &lt;craig@nnsc.nsf.net&gt;
     So, logically the nic would become something in *.defense-data.net
     or *.inter.net or something (I don't really care precisely what the
     second-level name is).

     Am I mistaken?


From: Bill Wohler &lt;wohler&gt;
  are we talking about the same nic here?  logically the nic might be
  in the net domain, but it might also be in any number of other
  domains as well.  physically (and financially) the nic is here at
  SRI International so nic.sri.com seems to be the most logical name
  to pick.

  if the nic were an independent enterprise, i would see your point,
  but trying to give different names to hosts at the same institution
  would make things confusing.  does it seem reasonable, as craig
  mentions, to have both *.inter.net hosts and *.sri.com hosts on the
  same class B network?

------- End of Forwarded Message

